    <h1>KIM KAR&#xAD;DASHIAN&#x2019;S SHAPEWEAR LINE JOINS NET-A-PORTER</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201204/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-04"><time>2020-12-04</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Fancy a fig­ure like Kim Kar­dashian West? You can buy the next best thing. The re­al­ity tele­vi­sion su­per­star’s line of shapewear, underwear and loungewear, Skims, launched on lux­ury e-tailer Net-aPorter on Tues­day.</p>
    <p>In ad­di­tion to its range of sculpt­ing shapewear called So­lu­tion­wear, the line of neu­tral-toned sta­ples in­cludes bras, pyjamas and tanks. Skims has been lauded for its in­clu­siv­ity of mul­ti­ple body shapes, with sizes from XXS to 4X (and up to 5X in So­lu­tion­wear), 31 cup sizes and nine tonal shades.</p>
    <p>Prices range from US$20 (S$26.70) for briefs to US$148 for a boucle robe.</p>
    <p>Net-a-Porter’s se­nior fash­ion mar­ket ed­i­tor Libby Page says: “Skims has com­pletely re­de­fined underwear and loungewear dress­ing, seam­lessly in­te­grat­ing the two worlds at a time when we need it most.”</p>
    <p>De­spite its pop­u­lar­ity now, the la­bel came un­der fire last year when it an­nounced its name was as Ki­mono. Many ac­cused Kar­dashian West of cul­tural ap­pro­pri­a­tion. Info: net-a-porter.com/en-sg/ shop/de­signer/skims</p>

